        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2474035845" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11732943589415776480"><strong>The definitive account of Day 1</strong><br/><br/>The author&apos;s detailed knowledge of the battle paired with his use of first-person testimony makes this book the definitive account of the battle. It reads like an thrilling play by play. I really recommend using a good battlefield atlas while reading this to follow all the action. Philip Laino&apos;s &quot;Gettysburg Campaign Atlas&quot; is what I used and it really brought the author&apos;s words to life. </span>
