        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer193133731" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2822029916754539886">A detailed analysis of the first day of the Battle of Gettysburg by a historian who already wrote book length studies of the struggles for Cemetary &amp; Culps Hills and the rest of the second day of the Battle of Gettysburg. He busts a lot of myths about the battle that have been repeated in various histories of the battle over the years. Well worth reading if you want to learn more about the Battle of Gettysburg than is covered by most single volume histories.<br/><br/><br/><br/>One thing that I found curious is that</span>
  <span id="freeText2822029916754539886" style="display:none">A detailed analysis of the first day of the Battle of Gettysburg by a historian who already wrote book length studies of the struggles for Cemetary &amp; Culps Hills and the rest of the second day of the Battle of Gettysburg. He busts a lot of myths about the battle that have been repeated in various histories of the battle over the years. Well worth reading if you want to learn more about the Battle of Gettysburg than is covered by most single volume histories.<br /><br /><br /><br />One thing that I found curious is that (unless I missed it) he didn't cite the earlier "Gettysburg July 1" by David G. Martin, even if the purpose of the citation is to disagree w/ some of Martin's conclusions.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2822029916754539886" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


