    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer339261255" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15059044844869349429">This book provides a very good account of the first day of the battle of Gettysburg. While it goes into many details, Pfanz was able to keep the narrative interesting and engaging. The main flaw in this book was the maps. Although its maps were better than many books, about twice as many would still have been fine and would have enhanced the story greatly. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


