<div id="review_63991973" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/63991973" />
    <a title="Avis Black" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/930189-avis-black"><img alt="Avis Black" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1204265491p2/930189.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/63991973?book_show_action=true">Jul 18, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Avis Black" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Avis Black" href="/user/show/930189-avis-black">Avis Black</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer63991973" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3591312804891762161">Pfanz suffers from extreme dullness of prose and a point of view in which he blithely accepts every convention about the battle of Gettysburg without investigating to see if the evidence supports these conventions or not. His analysis is simply awful.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

